    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Ilex cheniana are quercetin, a flavonoid with antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, quinic acid, a potential neuroprotective agent, isorhapontigenin, which exhibits anti-inflammatory and anti-oxidative effects, kaempferol, a flavonoid with anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties, and ilexgenin a, a lignan with antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities. These constituents are responsible for the medicinal properties of Ilex cheniana, including its use in traditional medicine for treating various health conditions. Quercetin and kaempferol have been shown to inhibit the growth of cancer cells and induce apoptosis, while isorhapontigenin and ilexgenin a have been found to reduce inflammation and oxidative stress. Quinic acid has been demonstrated to have neuroprotective effects, potentially preventing or slowing the progression of neurodegenerative diseases. The combination of these constituents in Ilex cheniana contributes to its overall therapeutic potential and supports its traditional use in medicine.",
