    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Ilex cheniana are typically made from its leaves, which have been used in traditional medicine. Ilex cheniana infusion is a method of steeping the leaves in hot water to extract its bioactive compounds. Ilex cheniana tea is a preparation similar to the infusion but often made with more leaves and steeped for a longer time to increase the concentration of the extracts. Ilex cheniana tincture is a concentrated liquid extract prepared by soaking the leaves in a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin. Ilex cheniana decoction is a preparation made by boiling the leaves in water to produce a more potent and longer-lasting extract, often used for its antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties.",
